						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone lying near the temple of Durgavva.</hi></p>						

						<p>This short inscription with no date states that this is the <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> field of <hi rend="italic">Sēnabōva</hi> <hi rend="bold">Narasiṁhadēva,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Tirumalabhaṭṭa</hi> of Maḷakhēḍa, who belonged to <hi rend="bold">Haṛita</hi>-<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Āpastaṁba</hi>-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Yajuś</hi>-<hi rend="italic">śākhā.</hi> The characters belong to the <hi rend="bold">16th century A.D.</hi></p>						

